cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the theoretical analysis of deep convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also addresses the problems of invariance, depth, and hierarchy in deep learning, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the architecture of ConvNets, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as text classification, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another possible sub-category.
